This is a C++ program that plays the game of Connect Four.
In one player mode, the human will play against the computer.
In two player mode, the program will allow each player to take turns.
Neither the number of columns nor the number of rows can be over 20.

Use below command to compile to program
g++ -std=c++11 connectfour.cpp -o connect_four

Use below command format to run the program
./connect_four <# of players> <# of columns> <# of rows>

Example command to start a two player game with 7 x 6 grid
./connect_four 2 7 6

Example command to start a one player game on 9 x 7 grid
./connect_four 1 9 7